1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with hand pose estimation using a CNN framework with a spatial attention mechanism. 
2. cs.RO (Robotics) is also likely as hand pose estimation is an important task in robotics for human-robot interaction. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper proposes a hybrid method that combines discriminative and generative methods using a hierarchical approach. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also possible as the paper deals with a task related to human perception and interaction, which is a common area of research in AI. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) is another possible category as the paper deals with 3D hand pose estimation, which is a common task in multimedia applications such as virtual and augmented reality.
